<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102573885854296></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102573885854296><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102573885854296>RE: DPS</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102573885854296#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id= >lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>107 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 3rd 7:38 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Haha.&nbsp;&nbsp;Reasoned yourself out of it?  =)<br><br>Actually, I think that you are correct in your 2nd post.  Double attack shouldnt play a role.  For instance, let's assume that Wurm had a DPS of 12 &amp; lammy had a DPS of 10, and your character had a 50% chance to double attack.  To determine which weapon would be better, you would increase the DPS of both weapons by 50%.  As such, you would adjust the DPS numbers as follows:<br><br>Wurm = 12 + (12*50%) = 18<br><br>Lammy = 10 + (10*50%) = 16<br><br>In this example, Wurm is still better when factoring in double attack.<br><br>Since you asked, the formula to calculate the percentage to double attack is as follows:<br><br>(Skill + Level) / 500.<br><br>The result should then be converted into a percentage.  As such, a lvl 50 character with 200 double attack skill has a 50% chance to double attack.<br><br>Re: Critical hits, see logic above.<br><br>Re: Duel wielding;  No, it is NOT true that a faster delay weapon gives duel wield a better chance to succeed.  You can put a lantern in your primary hand &amp; still get substantially the same results out of your offhand.  The formula, for those interested, to duel wield is as follows:<br><br>(Skill + Level) / 600 &amp; convert to a percentage, similar to double attack.  As such, a lvl 50 character, with a skill of 200 Duel wield, has a 41.67% chance to duel wield with the offhand.<br><br>It has nothing to do at all with what you are wielding in your primary hand.<br><br>As far as I know, delay is a measurement of time, stated in terms of seconds times 10.  So, in your example, yes, dly of 19 would be 1.9 secs.<br><br>Hope this helps  =P<br><br>Lunatic<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
