	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 1st 8:34 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>IKS SK?&nbsp;&nbsp;heh--decided to take the LONG ROAD (but honorable) (according to casters-realm, IKS / TRL SK are the slowest leveling race/class combo in the game!!  =P)<br><br>To be honest, with MoSS &amp; Fatecaller, I would NOT even worry about upgrading your weapon at all.  PP is something that is hard to get to the point where you can say, &quot;I have too much.&quot;  You will almost always find some armor / item that you will want to buy regardless of level &amp; there is a lot more to an SK than just a killer weapon (which you alrdy have for a character pre-50).<br><br>MoSS DPS is 13.4 &amp; Fatecaller is 14.9 (lvl bonus nor dmg cap factored into those figures mind you) &amp; those weapons will easily carry you THROUGH your 40s &amp; not be embarassed.  If you were able to get together some PP &amp; couldnt stand it, I would go for a Noct Blade, or, even better, Ebon Mace.<br><br>Keep in mind, however, that I prefer, by a small margin, 1H weapons to 2H weapons for any SK class NOT an ORG/TRL, so you can bash &amp; interrupt spell casting MOBs (ORG/TRL get slam--no other SK races get that).  Further, a 1H weapon will generally allow you to tank better as your AC will be much higher cause of the shield.<br><br>A 1H weapon, however, will have a hard time outdamaging an equivalent 2H weapon, especially if that 2H weapon is long delay, high damage (primarily due to lvl bonus).  Additionally, a 2H is generally more efficient to cast spells with (in between swings--taking advantage of slow swing time).<br><br>As far as how hard you will hit, hell, Im not sure what the silly caps are anymore; I havent had to deal with them for a long time  =P.  Over 100 at 20?  Perhaps, but probably not.  You will in your 30s i think.  I honestly cant remember anymore.  Perhaps someone else is better versed than I am at the damage caps at 20.<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
