	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 1st 11:46 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Believe it or not you get to add both the range of the bow and the arrow to get range.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, a bow with range of 150 and an arrow with range of 125 means that you get a total range of 275.  <br><br>This is one of the main reasons why bow are not necessarily a bad weapon for a Shadow Knight.  When pulling a bow may give you a lot of distance in comparison to a spell.<br><br>Good Hunting...<br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
