<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102552609739474></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102552609739474><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102552609739474>RE: dexterity</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102552609739474#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>207 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 1st 8:31 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dexterity is a nice stat to have, but won't give a huge increase your effectiveness.&nbsp;&nbsp;The higher your level the more Dex will help, as you get better and better Procs as you level.  However it seems to take 15 to 30 extra dex to see any difference in procs.<br><br>For me I only really notice a better proc rate going from under 100 to over 100 DEX and then if I break 150 Dex with buffs.  One of the parsers may give you a more definative answer but over-all I wouldn't intentionally go for DEX over STR or STA unless I was close and wanted to break 100 DEX or if you were under 75 DEX.  That seem to be the breaking point for all stats, below 75 you get a penalty above 100 you see a little bit better bonus of some kind.<br><br>Otherwise level will naturally increase proc rates on your self buff taps.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
