	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well you might as well get both sides of this here, me and Lunatic have a slightly different perspective on Stats and gear.<br><br>First I'll say concentrate on Stamina to get over 100.&nbsp;&nbsp;That is the magic number where you don't slow down attacks when your yellow bar goes away.  After that Stamina is not that important because it doesn't add that many HP's over-all.  I would instead focus on AC and in the lower levels Strength.  AC is king, it is what will mean the differance from being hit for 50 and being hit for 30, and the lower the hits the more likely you are to channel thru them and get your fear to caste.<br><br>Next for soloing, Fear-Kiting (reverse-kiting) is the way to go, and to do that you need mana.  Until lvl 30, you will probably get more mana from +mana items like moonstone rings that INT items.  But I will say when given a choice between an item with +mana and no AC and a +INT item with AC, go for the AC.  For this things like 1 Sentient Bracer is nice (good AC and +INT).  I also try to avoid Crusty armor as much as possible, I hate the loss of DEX and the AC is lower than the other Plate Armors availible.  I'd instead look for maybe 1 or 2 pieces of Crusty (Helm, Bracer maybe the legs as they have a huge STA increase but take DEX) and then get Darkforge and Sentient for the rest.  The Bracer of Scavenging is also a really good item to offset the negative DEX on Crusty.  The other stuff to look for to fill in would be spider fur for belt, neck and back for good ac/stats.<br><br>Other options will help after level 25 or so.  For example once the Damage Cap comes off and further post lvl 30 when you start seeing bigger 2hs bonuses using a 2 hand weapon while fear-kiting will result in faster kills.  Also after lvl 30 the + INT stuff generally starts giving more mana than the + mana items.<br><br>good luck.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
