	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, yes, um no and ok.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes I understand and agree with your assessment for Fear Kiting, excetp that I still think AC is important as I stated for being able to channel thru hits to get fear to work.  Yes I would give up stamina for Ac as well keeping over 100.<br><br>But no, Clerics are great for fear kiting.  Let them fear (they get fear as well), let them stun and DD and with them you will get very little down time.  They can also keep the pet alive if you have a low add, letting the pet tank an add for a short time while you finish off the primary MOB.  About the only better partners I had for fear-kiting was Druids (snare/ds) and Shaman (buffs/slows), Clerics are by far better than the rest.<br><br>As for the core stats, I do not agree that Stamina is the core stat.  I know others agree with you, I will only say it is one of the core stats.  The amount of HPs you can gain from putting al your points into Stamina will still not make you a Warrior, so I perfer to concentrate in other areas and play my SK accordingly.  I started with 70 Stamina and I still tank every bit as well as the Ogre SK's I have played with.  But ok, if someone puts all their points into Stamina it wil not make them a useless SK, just slightly handicapped in the casting department.  Putting all your points into STA for an Ogre/Troll and then trying to solo alot is a bad deal, if you always plan on grouping it will help you till lvl 51 but no further.  After lvl 51 Warriors get so many more HPs per Stamina that we just can't ever get close and I'd rather have more mana for snares, debuffs and taps.  But again if you want to go Stamina OK.<br><br>I agree with you about what he should uses for fear-kiting.  But I would almost never recommend full Crusty as the AC is alot lower than Sentient.  There have been times people have said they already had it that I agree it's a good set, but to buy an entire set is not a good idea for loss of DEX and too low AC (Ry`Gorr has higher AC), the Stamina as a whole is not worth the negatives for me.  Even if he is Tanking I'd take the Sentient of 90% of the Crusty, and I think that is where we disagree.<br><br>Either way he's got enough info now to make his own choice.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
