	   <tr><td colspan=2>Killing hill giants in Rathe mountains was actually a pretty easy place for my sk to solo in during the 40's.&nbsp;&nbsp;Made some decent cash and decent exp till I got up to 47 or so.  Just make sure ya have a decent range bow so you can out pull all the annoying, quad-happy tree huggers.  Also good if you can get a shammy, chanter, or cleric partner.  <br><br>Also got some decent exp in dawnshroud peaks soloing the tribal dudes outside the ME zone in my low 40's.  Made a couple bucks selling the backpacks full of polished steel ulaks i'd collect as well.<br><br>Eastern wastes is a fear kiter's paradise.  Plenty of open room and lots of decent exp to be made there as well for a lone sk.  Get a cleric partner and maybe pick up a chanter and you move your exp bar with some serious wholesale slaughter in crystal cavers also.<br><br>As far as grouping is concerned, dreadlands exp seems to move kinda slow unless you get in a crazy over pulling group that knows what it's doing.  A good group there can spend several hours with non stop pulls and no down time.  Uusally with half a dozen mezzed mobs on stand-by and so many bodies rotting you cant see the ground.  Was always a trip.  <br><br>A pair of sk's can pretty much rock anywhere there's room to fearkite and dark blue mobs.  While one pulls, the other meds.  When the puller gets back to the camp spot with a mob, he tanks it for a lil bit while the other sk darks/fears.  Then you both proceed to sic your pets and start beating the crap out of the poor mob untill it's dead.  Then the previous puller meds while the previous medder goes hunting.  Can generally pull all night long with little down time and nice exp.<br>Add in a chanter and watch the exp fly by.  Same group can make a fortune of plat and some really nice exp in rathe mountains slaughtering hill giants.<br><br>Just a few suggestions.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
