	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.53]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I actually was one of the boring ones---&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>As OT &amp; DL, for me at least, were very easy to get a group, I probably got say, 90% of my xp from 30ish to 50ish from those zones alone.  Haha--not a lot of variety, but my goal was to level, not scout other zones, so there I stayed...<br><br>As far as armor is concerned, sure you can wait until lvl 46ish for better armor.  The next step up that I would consider, once you reach 46ish, is twofold:  1) Thurg armor (called Dark Runed--excellent AC, NOT excellent buffs---kill in Kael for armor drops (Riff house, Arena, etc), then get the annoying gems from either auction or other zones in Velious). or 2) Plane of Growth (PoG) (called Noct armor (abbreviated)--is as good as Thurg armor.  PoG is probably faster to obtain (better drop rates) and doesnt require any gems.  There are several tricks/things that you need to be aware of when doing a PoG raid however.  For instance, you will probably need some high level tanks for the Protectors of Growth that spawn every 28ish minutes (they have zone wide agro), pulling the East side of the river isnt exactly simple (ideally you want a BRD to pull--a CoHer is also highly recommended), and trying to find some CLRs willing to trash GFAY faction is NOT easy (HIE CLRs worship Tunare)--all of these are a PAIN in the arse for PoG raids, but they sure are fun when you get there.....)<br><br>As far as solo or group, I soloed a little bit in OT &amp; DL both, but found that a group was more entertaining, as the pulls were much faster.  Furthermore, I also found that being in a group was far less risky.<br><br>There is often a debate as to which is a faster way to obtain XP--solo or in a group.  Fighting solo, the xp is all yours, however, the pulls are much slower as your DPS is not going to be as good as with say 5 others.  A group would pretty much be the exact opposite.  However, a group generally is far safer than solo, so I chose a group to get most of my xp.  <br><br>The one exception to this is the WIZ or DRD who can do their ANNOYING QUAD PULLING, which clearly will level faster than any other normal tactics (WIZ AE groups another exception).  Why do I say ANNOYING?  Try fighting in Cobalt Scar or a zone where they can quad pull--the MOBs become thin really quick then you have like 5 people all running to the next MOB for the next pull.  KSing in here is common.  At least when I pull, Im only pulling one, leaving all the other MOBs there for the taking.  They pull friggin FOUR at a time, depleting the MOBs faster than we are destroying the rainforest.  Its the same annoying tactic too----snare, snare, snare, snare--run around like a wus to get them all together, then AoE their sorry arses.  It drives my nuts.  Partly because Im jealous, but also because I almost see it as arrogant or selfish--there are a lot of people looking for MOBs to kill &amp; they start wiping them out at an alarming rate--it doesnt bug me when there isnt a lot of people in the zone, but when its packed, its just annoying.  Im not sure what I would do if I was a WIZ or DRD hunting at that level, but I probably would NOT do those annoying tactics because I understand what it is like to be on the other side....<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
