<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102450768869002></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102450768869002><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102450768869002>RE: Clinging Darkness & Engulfing Darkness</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102450768869002#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id= >lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>107 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 19th 1:37 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sure you can cast both clinging darkness &amp; engulfing darkness on a mob, but they will not stack--I think that engulfing will overwrite clinging.<br><br>On a marginally unrelated note, engulfing is a good snare for when you are in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;I use it now even in SEB, Velks, etc due to the quicker casting time over dooming (4 secs vs. 2.45 secs).  If I am acting as the snarer of my group, I mem engulfing every time.  Knock on wood, I haven&amp;#8217;t had a problem yet with engulfing.<br><br>Dooming, however, is DEFENITELY the way to go when fear-kiting.  Dooming makes fear-kiting about 1000x easier because there is quite a noticeable difference between the run rate of the mob when dooming is on him (dooming is 20% better, from 40% reduction in run rate for engulfing to 60% with dooming) and it lasts twice as long (assuming no break in the snare, 2 min for engulfing vs. 4 min for dooming).  The MOB practically crawls to you (and then away when you fear him).<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Lunatic<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
